<a id="top"> </a><h1>K.D. Irani Professor of Philosophy, The City College, City University of New York</h1>
<p>
The Department of Philosophy at The City College of the City University of New York 
seeks to appoint the K. D. Irani Professor of Philosophy. This is an endowed Chair. 
AOS: Philosophy of Science, Technology, and Society. Qualified candidates in any 
(or any combination) of these areas are invited to apply. The Irani Chair entails a full 
Professorship in the Department of Philosophy at CCNY, along with research and travel 
funds attached to the endowment. The successful candidate will teach undergraduate 
philosophy courses at introductory and advanced levels. Preference will be given to 
candidates interested in collaborating with faculty in the sciences and in teaching (other 
than Applied Ethics) CCNY students in Architecture, Engineering, and/or the Physical \
and Life Sciences.
</p>
<p>
Applicants are requested to submit an application letter, full c.v., and six references
online (Job Opening 8961) at <a href="http://www.cuny.edu" rel="external">http://www.cuny.edu</a>. 
Please upload all materials as a single PDF document.
</p>
